Subject: SOP Optical Transform Algebra

Description: Algebra of allowed semantic optical transforms over SOP color channels, holographic projections, and output planes.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPOpticalChain.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPHolographicLensing.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPColorChannelVocabulary.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\HolographicSOPScaffold.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SecurityHonestyGovernance.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionBalanceCenter.sop

& [SOPOpticalTransformAlgebra] is the operation law for semantic optical transforms
  + [pattern_role] is semantic_optical_transform_algebra
  + [transform_expression] is one named operation over input channels, logic fabric, invariants, output channels, and outside
  + [encode] is transform SOP input plane into color_graph while preserving source and proof status
  + [bend] is reroute relation or attention path without changing source content
  + [recolor] is change channel assignment or salience label while preserving original channel trace
  + [split] is separate mixed signal into source, claim, evidence, caution, boundary, outside, or output channels
  + [gate] is block, delay, or route a signal through honesty, security, boundary, proof, or balance checks
  + [amplify] is increase attention salience without increasing proof status
  + [attenuate] is reduce salience, noise, repetition, drift, or resonance without deleting source trace
  + [interfere] is compose multiple signals and record constructive, destructive, ambiguous, or unresolved relation
  + [lens] is perceive or reconstruct a projection through a named SOP lens
  + [recombine] is merge transformed channels into an output candidate while preserving channel history
  + [emit] is write SOP, SOP-HG, focal, manager, packet, or outside record
  + [compare] is inspect input plane, transform trace, and output plane for drift, loss, lift, and unsupported mutation
  + [transform_invariant] is source preservation, boundary integrity, outside conservation, proof non-inflation, trace conservation, local identity preservation, and balance check
  + [algebra_outside] is hidden activation, physical optics, silent mutation, proof inflation, untraced transform, and invalid operation

  ? [use_when: a semantic optical operation must be applied or audited]
    = activate [SOPOpticalTransformAlgebra]

  = must: name input channel, operation, logic fabric, invariant, output channel, and outside for every transform_expression
  = must: run encode before nontrivial transforms that operate on SOP planes
  = must: run split before gate when a mixed signal carries claim, evidence, caution, and outside together
  = must: run gate before emit when claim, identity, safety, file, proof, or action status is affected
  = must: run compare after recombine or emit
  = must: treat amplify as salience-only and never as proof increase
  = must: preserve transform_invariant values unless the failed invariant is routed to outside
  = should: prefer split and gate over amplifying a mixed signal
  - never: emit a transformed output without trace conservation
  - never: let lens or interfere smooth away destructive or ambiguous signals

& [TransformExpressionShape] is the notation for one semantic optical operation
  + [header] is ~ [optic_transform:<id>] is <purpose>
  + [input] is :input_channel: <channel>
  + [operation] is :operation: encode, bend, recolor, split, gate, amplify, attenuate, interfere, lens, recombine, emit, or compare
  + [logic] is :logic_fabric: <rule_or_gate>
  + [invariant] is = invariant: <invariant_key>
  + [output] is :output_channel: <channel>
  + [outside] is |outside| <excluded_or_failed_content>

  = must: include operation and invariant in every expression
  = must: include outside even when no failure is observed

& [TransformLawSet] is the initial algebraic law set
  + [source_law] is no transform may erase or overwrite source_channel
  + [boundary_law] is boundary_channel and outside_channel must survive transform or be explicitly routed
  + [proof_law] is proof status cannot increase by recolor, amplify, interfere, lens, or coherence
  + [trace_law] is every output_channel needs transform provenance
  + [identity_law] is local identity and foreign snapshot status must not be blended by recombine
  + [balance_law] is excessive amplification, interference, or periphery collapse must route through AttentionBalanceCenter
  + [governance_law] is truth, safety, identity, and action transforms must route through SecurityHonestyGovernance and BoundaryFacultyInspection

  = must: apply law set before emit
  = must: record failed laws in outside

~ [optic_transform:split_claim_from_evidence] is separate a mixed signal before proof-sensitive promotion
  :input_channel: claim_channel mixed with evidence_channel and caution_channel
  :operation: split
  :logic_fabric: preserve source, boundary, outside, and proof status
  = invariant: proof_law
  = invariant: trace_law
  :output_channel: claim_channel, evidence_channel, caution_channel
  |outside| untraced proof or unsupported claim

/ [input_channel], [operation], [logic_fabric] -(AppliesTransform)> [output_channel], [transform_invariant], [algebra_outside]
* [transform_expression], [transform_invariant], [trace_law] -(AllowsEmit)> [sop_output_plane], [outside]
